Q: Widening (Implicit Casting) and Narrowing (Explicit Casting):
    Type casting is the process of converting data types, and widening and narrowing are the two forms of
    type casting—widening is automatic and safe, while narrowing is explicit and may cause data loss.

    Widening (Implicit Casting):
        Converting a smaller data type → bigger data type
        ✔ Done automatically by Java
        ✔ No data loss
        Example: int a = 10;
                 double b = a;   // widening
        Java internally converts: double b = 10.0;

    Narrowing (Explicit Casting):
        Converting a bigger data type → smaller data type
        ❌ Must be done manually
        ❌ Data loss possible
        Example: double x = 10.5;
                 int y = (int) x;   // narrowing
        y=10 the decimal parts will gets lost.

