StringBuilder and StringBuffer:
    StringBuilder is fast but not thread-safe,
    StringBuffer is thread-safe but slower.

    Problem with String:
        String s = "Hello";
        s = s + " World";

    ❌ This creates new objects again and again
    ❌ Memory waste
    ❌ Slow in loops

    Solution: Mutable strings and That’s where StringBuilder and StringBuffer come in.


        | Class         |  Mutable? |  Thread-safe? |
        | ------------- | ----------| ------------- |
        | String        | ❌ No     | ✅ Yes        |
        | StringBuilder | ✅ Yes    | ❌ No         |
        | StringBuffer  | ✅ Yes    | ✅ Yes        |

Some inbuild methods of this:

        | Method                      | Description                            | Example                  |
        | --------------------------- | -------------------------------------- | ------------------------ |
        | `append(x)`                 | Adds value at the end                  | `sb.append("Java")`      |
        | `insert(int, x)`            | Inserts value at given index           | `sb.insert(4, "Hello")`  |
        | `delete(int, int)`          | Removes characters from start to end-1 | `sb.delete(0, 3)`        |
        | `deleteCharAt(int)`         | Removes character at index             | `sb.deleteCharAt(2)`     |
        | `replace(int, int, String)` | Replaces characters                    | `sb.replace(0, 4, "Hi")` |
        | `reverse()`                 | Reverses the sequence                  | `sb.reverse()`           |
        | `length()`                  | Returns number of characters           | `sb.length()`            |
        | `capacity()`                | Returns current capacity               | `sb.capacity()`          |
        | `ensureCapacity(int)`       | Ensures minimum capacity               | `sb.ensureCapacity(50)`  |
        | `setLength(int)`            | Changes length (truncate/extend)       | `sb.setLength(5)`        |
        | `charAt(int)`               | Returns char at index                  | `sb.charAt(1)`           |
        | `setCharAt(int, char)`      | Replaces char at index                 | `sb.setCharAt(1,'A')`    |
        | `substring(int)`            | Substring from index                   | `sb.substring(3)`        |
        | `substring(int, int)`       | Substring between indexes              | `sb.substring(1,4)`      |
        | `indexOf(String)`           | First index of string                  | `sb.indexOf("Java")`     |
        | `indexOf(String, int)`      | Index from position                    | `sb.indexOf("a",2)`      |
        | `lastIndexOf(String)`       | Last occurrence                        | `sb.lastIndexOf("a")`    |
        | `lastIndexOf(String, int)`  | Last occurrence before index           | `sb.lastIndexOf("a",5)`  |
        | `toString()`                | Converts to `String`                   | `sb.toString()`          |
        | `compareTo(StringBuilder)`  | Lexicographical compare                | `sb1.compareTo(sb2)`     |
        | `chars()`                   | Returns IntStream of chars             | `sb.chars()`             |
        | `codePoints()`              | Unicode code points                    | `sb.codePoints()`        |

