Serialization & Deserialization:
    - Serialization is the process of converting an object into a byte stream so it can be saved to a file or transferred
      over a network, and deserialization restores it back to an object.

Q: How serialization works internally?
    Java provides:
    - ObjectOutputStream → serialize object
    - ObjectInputStream → deserialize object

    But Java needs to know:
    “Is this object allowed to be serialized?”

    - That’s why we use Serializable interface.

